cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper proposes a new secure system model and two cooperative jamming based schemes to maximize the secrecy rate and minimize the transmit power, which are related to information theory.
2. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper focuses on enhancing physical security in public transportation networks, which is related to cryptography and security.
3. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper proposes a wireless power transfer and cooperative jamming based system model for public transportation networks, which is related to networking and internet architecture.
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a new system model with fixed and mobile jammers, which is related to systems and control.
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper uses simulation results to evaluate the proposed schemes, which is related to multimedia.
